Chilean Stocks: Empresas CMPC, Sonda and Sudamericana de Vapores

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-09-13T19:47:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-13/chilean-stocks-empresas-cmpc-sonda-and-sudamericana-de-vapores.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 3:14 p.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index rose 0.5 percent to 4,031.33.  Cia. Sudamericana de Vapores SA (VAPORES CC),  Latin
America ’s largest container shipping company, fell 1.6 percent
to 153.33 pesos, its lowest price since March 1999. Holding
companies  Quinenco SA (QUINENC)  and Maritima de Inversiones SA, which own
about 41 percent of Vapores’s shares, signed a new shareholder
agreement yesterday to control the company, according to a
statement posted on the website of the Santiago stock exchange.  Quinenco SA (QUINENC CC) led losses among members of the
Ipsa index, with a 4.4 percent fall to 1,233.4 pesos, the
biggest drop in more than a month.  Empresas CMPC SA (CMPC)  ,  Chile ’s second-largest pulp
exporter, rose 0.4 percent to 18,255 pesos. A 10-for-1 stock
split will come into effect Sept. 16, according to a paid
advertisement published in today’s edition of Diario Financiero.  Sonda SA (SONDA)   gained 2.1 percent to 1,189 pesos.
Chile’s largest information technology provider secured an 89
percent stake in local rival Quintec SA as part of a public
tender offer, according to a paid advert published yesterday on
local newspaper La Tercera.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
